snippet.textDisplay:
That back wall isn't that scary. Just big. I saved a barn that the bottom 4 feet all the way around was gone. I did it one small section at a time. I would brace it top to bottom. Make sure you're carrying loads all the way to the ground. I wouldn't trust anything there to hold.


You really need to start on the back. Save the easy stuff for later. You need to see what kinda shape the 2nd floor floor joist are in. Do the flooring and joist have issues? It will be interesting to see what all is damaged. I have a feeling you will have some joist and flooring that need to be replaced.


Do nails rot out faster than wood? How much rot around the nail do you need before the nail is compromised? You should think about nailing some of the wood that is staying. It may look ok but how strong is it? I don't know.
